The paper discusses a new operator for enhancing the Graph Convolutional Network (GCN) for feature learning on graph data. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) as it involves designing a new operator for improving the performance of a machine learning technique. Additionally, the paper mentions several tasks such as recommendation and linked document classification, which are commonly associated with artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments conducted in the paper involve working with graphs and analyzing their features, which is relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper also discusses the utility of explicitly modeling cross features, which is relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR).
